refsect2.para:
gdbus functions will be used frequently. To avoid excessive typing, the following functions should be defined and called:
# function to begin registration begin() { gdbus call --system \ -d org.genivi.NodeStartupController1 \ -o /org/genivi/NodeStartupController1/NodeStartupController \ -m org.genivi.NodeStartupController1.NodeStartupController.BeginLUCRegistration \ }
# function to make a registration call register() { gdbus call --system \ -d org.genivi.NodeStartupController1 \ -o /org/genivi/NodeStartupController1/NodeStartupController \ -m org.genivi.NodeStartupController1.NodeStartupController.RegisterWithLUC \ "$1" }
# function to finish registration end() { gdbus call --system \ -d org.genivi.NodeStartupController1 \ -o /org/genivi/NodeStartupController1/NodeStartupController \ -m org.genivi.NodeStartupController1.NodeStartupController.FinishLUCRegistration \ }
